Deputy President William Ruto and his wife Rachel Ruto at their Karen residence before leaving for Kasarani Stadium on Tuesday, March 15. [Standard]  The United Democratic Alliance (UDA) Party has endorsed Deputy President William Ruto for President.  At least 4,350 UDA delegates on Tuesday, March 15 unanimously endorsed Ruto’s candidature in the August 9 presidential election.  The NDC was held at the Moi International Sports Complex, Kasarani.  After being crowned the party’s flagbearer in the upcoming polls, Ruto is expected to embark on a search for his running mate and to forge coalition with other like-minded parties. Safina Party presidential aspirant Jimi Wanjigi, formerly of ODM, and Chama Cha Kazi’s Moses Kuria attended the NDC at Kasarani Stadium.  By Stephanie Wangari | 1 hour ago By Dennis Tarus | 1 hour ago By Stephanie Wangari | 2 hours ago By Patrick Vidija | 2 hours ago